Overview

This tool runs a deep-research agent to process queries, perform literature and web searches, and generate structured reports.

Prerequisites

• Python 3.8 or later  
• A valid GEMINI_API key (set as an environment variable) , Note : A API key is already present in code.

Installation

1. Create and activate a virtual environment:
   • Unix/macOS:
   python -m venv venv
   source venv/bin/activate
   • Windows:
   python -m venv venv
   venv\Scripts\activate

2. Install dependencies:
   pip install -r requirements.txt

Usage

1. Ensure your GEMINI_API key is set (or configure it in config.py).
2. Run the main script:
   python main.py
3. Follow the interactive prompts to enter your research query and confirm tasks.

Outputs

cot.log
Detailed chain-of-thought logs for each summarization step.

Report.json
JSON-formatted structured results.

final_report.md
Human-readable Markdown report generated from Report.json.

Troubleshooting

• If you see 429 Too Many Requests, reduce query rate or update API quotas.

